<h2>What is this?</h2>

<p>
The <i>Koch-Suite</i> is an <i>PHP</i>-based
<i>recipe management system</i> for Unix-like Operatingsystems.
It uses MySQL or PostgreSQL as database-backend.

The License is BSD-style (three-clause) and therefore
<a href="http://www.opensource.org">Opensource</a>.

Tested and supported are currently the Operating Systems
Linux, <a href="http://www.openbsd.org">OpenBSD</a> and <a
href="http://www.freebsd.org">FreeBSD</a>. The
<i>Koch-Suite</i> should run on other Operating Systems, too, it just
isn't tested until now.
</p>

